{
  "texts": [
    "The interval of invariant mass to which the histogram refers is indicated above the histogram.",
    "The bands show the scale uncertainty.",
    "Figure 4:4Figure 4: Integrated PDFs for down quarks obtained from the PB-NLO-2018 Set2 TMD, with q 0 ≃ 0 GeV (red histogram) and q 0 = 1 GeV (blue histogram) and their ratios, for two scale values: µ = 70 GeV (left) and µ = 400 GeV (right).",
    "Figure 5:5Figure 5: Integrated PDFs for down quarks obtained from the PB-NLO-2018 Set2 TMD, with q 0 ≃ 0 GeV (red histogram) and q 0 = 1 GeV (blue histogram) and their ratios, for two scale values: µ = 70 GeV (left) and µ = 400 GeV (right).",
    "Figure 6:6Figure 6: Intrinsic k T width as a function of DY pair invariant mass, obtained from the comparison of CASCADE 3 predictions with two values of q 0 and measurements obtained at √ s = 27.4 GeV [21] (left) and √ s = 38.8 GeV [22] (right)."
